George Dinwiddie wrote:
&gt; Coming back to an old topic, were you using container-managed
&gt; or bean-managed persistence, here?
&gt; 
&gt; The reason I ask is that my project has now mandated EJB 2.0
&gt; CMP and I&#39;m trying to figure out how I can create instantiable
&gt; objects with the business logic, when access to the persistent
&gt; fields are all abstract methods.

I&#39;m using CMP.

The trick is that my local implementation declares the methods as
non-abstract, then the EJB implementation (descended from it) redeclares
them as abstract.

Robert.

